1
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:12,280
<i>Help.</i>

2
00:00:14,120 --> 00:00:16,959
<i>You just lost Ms. Claire, your fiancée,</i>

3
00:00:16,960 --> 00:00:17,999
Don't you feel anything?

4
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:20,079
I wanted Claire dead too.

5
00:00:20,080 --> 00:00:22,319
<i>She made him think I cheated on him.</i>

6
00:00:22,320 --> 00:00:24,759
<i>Ever since that day,
your dad's been cold to me.</i>

7
00:00:24,760 --> 00:00:25,999
<i>Why would Rin want to hurt me?</i>

8
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:29,439
She doesn't want to hurt you.
She wants to hurt Claire.

9
00:00:29,440 --> 00:00:31,759
<i>We need to keep
a closer eye on Ms. Rossarin.</i>

10
00:00:31,760 --> 00:00:35,920
What we need to do from here on out
is protect her as best as we can.

11
00:00:41,360 --> 00:00:43,839
<i>- Ms. Claire, please!
- I said stay still.</i>

12
00:00:43,840 --> 00:00:46,639
<i>- I said stay still.
- Please, Ms. Claire, no!</i>

13
00:00:46,640 --> 00:00:47,759
<i>Ms. Claire!</i>

14
00:00:47,760 --> 00:00:48,959
<i>Ms. Claire, please!</i>

15
00:00:48,960 --> 00:00:51,920
<i>Ms. Claire, please, don't do that!</i>

16
00:00:54,400 --> 00:00:58,199
No wonder they look terrified
whenever I walk past them.

17
00:00:58,200 --> 00:01:01,479
<i>This is absolute garbage!
How many times have I told you?</i>

18
00:01:01,480 --> 00:01:03,679
<i>You're so stupid! So freaking stupid!</i>

19
00:01:03,680 --> 00:01:05,640
<i>I don't even know what to say!</i>

20
00:01:06,160 --> 00:01:08,120
<i>- I'm sorry.
- How many times have I told you?</i>

21
00:01:09,560 --> 00:01:10,600
Ms. Claire!

22
00:01:13,560 --> 00:01:14,680
Ms. Claire!

23
00:01:16,840 --> 00:01:18,079
- Nitchan.
- <i>Is this all you can do?</i>

24
00:01:18,080 --> 00:01:21,319
Were you really gonna
marry someone like her?

25
00:01:21,320 --> 00:01:22,320
<i>Go!</i>

26
00:01:23,080 --> 00:01:24,279
<i>What are you looking at?</i>

27
00:01:24,280 --> 00:01:25,400
<i>Get back to work.</i>

28
00:01:43,280 --> 00:01:44,240
Where are you going?

29
00:01:46,400 --> 00:01:48,880
Jeez, you scared me,
sneaking up like that.

30
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:53,120
I...

31
00:01:54,240 --> 00:01:56,560
I was on my way to see Mr. Chan.

32
00:01:57,240 --> 00:01:58,600
Is something the matter?

33
00:01:59,640 --> 00:02:01,440
I have some questions for him.

34
00:02:04,200 --> 00:02:07,320
Actually, I might get more from you.

35
00:02:08,720 --> 00:02:09,720
What is it about?

36
00:02:11,840 --> 00:02:13,719
It's about Mr. Chan.

37
00:02:13,720 --> 00:02:16,239
He showed me Ms. Claire's profile,

38
00:02:16,240 --> 00:02:18,799
but I didn't see any info on him.

39
00:02:18,800 --> 00:02:21,319
Even though he's Claire's fiancé.

40
00:02:21,320 --> 00:02:23,960
You know him, right? Can you fill me in?

41
00:02:25,200 --> 00:02:28,240
Mr. Chan must have his reasons
for keeping it from you.

42
00:02:30,240 --> 00:02:32,440
If he really wants me to be Claire,

43
00:02:33,080 --> 00:02:35,280
he should at least share his info with me.

44
00:02:35,880 --> 00:02:38,919
I'm not asking for anything too deep.

45
00:02:38,920 --> 00:02:41,999
I just want to know
who he is and where he's from.

46
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:44,399
Oh, if I had to guess,

47
00:02:44,400 --> 00:02:46,760
he must be a really perfect man.

48
00:02:48,880 --> 00:02:49,720
Not really.

49
00:02:51,840 --> 00:02:54,040
He's the son of the chairman's driver.

50
00:02:55,280 --> 00:02:56,960
A driver's son?

51
00:02:59,800 --> 00:03:00,800
So...

52
00:03:01,320 --> 00:03:03,680
why did she agree to marry him?

53
00:03:09,640 --> 00:03:12,200
Shi, look. I'll throw the balls.

54
00:03:17,640 --> 00:03:19,040
Let's get married.

55
00:03:20,960 --> 00:03:21,999
No way.

56
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:23,759
Why not?

57
00:03:23,760 --> 00:03:28,199
My dad said you're the boss
and I'm an employee.

58
00:03:28,200 --> 00:03:29,959
So we can't get married?

59
00:03:29,960 --> 00:03:31,280
No.

60
00:03:31,960 --> 00:03:35,559
No, I will only marry you! Nobody else!

61
00:03:35,560 --> 00:03:37,719
No!

62
00:03:37,720 --> 00:03:40,679
- I have to marry you!
- Fine, I'll marry you.

63
00:03:40,680 --> 00:03:41,760
Promise?

64
00:03:42,480 --> 00:03:44,040
‎Yay!

65
00:03:46,080 --> 00:03:47,120
Here.

66
00:03:48,080 --> 00:03:49,600
Put it on me.

67
00:03:54,960 --> 00:03:58,560
<i>When you grow up,
you can't marry anyone but me.</i>

68
00:04:00,080 --> 00:04:01,160
Promise me.

69
00:04:01,680 --> 00:04:02,840
I promise.

70
00:04:21,079 --> 00:04:22,759
And...

71
00:04:22,760 --> 00:04:26,880
didn't her grandfather object to her
marrying a driver's son like Mr. Chan?

72
00:04:27,840 --> 00:04:28,919
Not at all.

73
00:04:28,920 --> 00:04:32,040
The chairman was even
thrilled and supported them

74
00:04:32,640 --> 00:04:37,399
because Mr. Chan's father had been
driving for him since TGL's early days.

75
00:04:37,400 --> 00:04:40,439
So he loves Mr. Chan like his own son.

76
00:04:40,440 --> 00:04:41,359
- Then why...
- Beep!

77
00:04:41,360 --> 00:04:42,720
Your time's up.

78
00:04:43,920 --> 00:04:45,920
You should go back to your room.

79
00:04:46,560 --> 00:04:50,319
If Mr. Chan catches you out here,
he might get angry at you again.

80
00:04:50,320 --> 00:04:52,360
- I just--
- And if you have questions,

81
00:04:52,880 --> 00:04:55,240
it's better to ask him directly.

82
00:04:57,440 --> 00:04:59,240
Let's go. Please.

83
00:06:32,680 --> 00:06:33,920
This way, Mr. Chris.

84
00:06:35,640 --> 00:06:37,559
I'll wait in the living room.

85
00:06:37,560 --> 00:06:40,080
Sure. Would you like something to drink?

86
00:06:41,080 --> 00:06:42,720
- Water.
- Yes, sir.

87
00:07:07,800 --> 00:07:08,640
Cha.

88
00:07:09,960 --> 00:07:11,280
Cha.

89
00:07:12,920 --> 00:07:14,360
Cha, I'm sorry.

90
00:07:15,320 --> 00:07:16,160
Cha.

91
00:07:42,960 --> 00:07:44,199
Who is that water for?

92
00:07:44,200 --> 00:07:46,039
Mr. Chris is here to see Ms. Cha,

93
00:07:46,040 --> 00:07:49,640
but she isn't back yet.
So he's waiting in the living room.

94
00:07:54,400 --> 00:07:55,760
Thank you.

95
00:08:29,360 --> 00:08:30,480
Ms. Claire?

96
00:08:34,600 --> 00:08:35,760
Ms. Claire.

97
00:08:49,280 --> 00:08:50,440
<i>Mr. Chris?</i>

98
00:08:52,720 --> 00:08:56,359
So, let's move on
to our final question, shall we?

99
00:08:56,360 --> 00:08:57,680
Sure.

100
00:08:59,640 --> 00:09:04,159
As one of Thailand's top architects,

101
00:09:04,160 --> 00:09:07,320
whom many aspiring architects
look up to as an idol,

102
00:09:08,160 --> 00:09:09,720
what about you?

103
00:09:10,240 --> 00:09:12,680
Do you have an idol of your own?

104
00:09:13,720 --> 00:09:14,680
It's you.

105
00:09:19,320 --> 00:09:20,200
Me?

106
00:09:21,440 --> 00:09:24,440
Oh, not really. I spoke too soon.

107
00:09:27,640 --> 00:09:28,760
For me,

108
00:09:30,920 --> 00:09:32,240
I think it's nature.

109
00:09:33,640 --> 00:09:35,440
Nature is what...

110
00:09:36,440 --> 00:09:38,280
created you this way,

111
00:09:39,480 --> 00:09:41,000
gave you this face.

112
00:09:42,120 --> 00:09:44,640
And it created me this way.

113
00:09:45,720 --> 00:09:49,440
I believe the greatest architect of all...

114
00:09:50,840 --> 00:09:51,800
is nature.

115
00:09:57,360 --> 00:10:01,320
<i>His words back then weren't fancy,</i>

116
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:03,679
<i>but somehow,</i>

117
00:10:03,680 --> 00:10:07,120
<i>I instantly felt a surge of inspiration.</i>

118
00:10:07,800 --> 00:10:11,239
<i>It made a woman
who was exhausted with life</i>

119
00:10:11,240 --> 00:10:13,520
<i>want to get back up and push forward.</i>

120
00:10:15,560 --> 00:10:16,760
<i>Or maybe...</i>

121
00:10:17,560 --> 00:10:19,080
<i>it was his smile.</i>

122
00:10:22,960 --> 00:10:25,640
<i>And now, I never imagined...</i>

123
00:10:26,240 --> 00:10:27,959
<i>he would be in front of me again.</i>

124
00:10:27,960 --> 00:10:29,360
Are you alright?

125
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:31,120
<i>Ms. Claire?</i>

126
00:10:32,400 --> 00:10:34,600
<i>Oh, right. I'm Ms. Claire now.</i>

127
00:10:36,200 --> 00:10:37,080
No, I'm fine.

128
00:10:38,160 --> 00:10:39,920
What brings you here, Mr. Chris?

129
00:10:40,920 --> 00:10:41,760
"Mr."?

130
00:10:43,520 --> 00:10:44,600
What about it?

131
00:10:45,520 --> 00:10:48,920
Well, you never called me that.

132
00:10:53,240 --> 00:10:57,479
I was in an accident,
so I have trouble remembering things.

133
00:10:57,480 --> 00:10:58,560
Ms. Claire.

134
00:11:02,600 --> 00:11:04,039
I was so worried about you.

135
00:11:04,040 --> 00:11:05,760
Mr. Chris, what are you doing?

136
00:11:06,680 --> 00:11:08,839
I thought I'd never see you again.

137
00:11:08,840 --> 00:11:10,479
<i>Why is he hugging me?</i>

138
00:11:10,480 --> 00:11:11,879
Wait, Mr. Chris.

139
00:11:11,880 --> 00:11:14,599
Wait, Mr. Chris, please let me go.

140
00:11:14,600 --> 00:11:16,640
Do you really not remember us?

141
00:11:17,440 --> 00:11:19,599
- No, I don't. I really don't.
- <i>Or...</i>

142
00:11:19,600 --> 00:11:21,999
- Claire...
- <i>...were they actually...</i>

143
00:11:22,000 --> 00:11:23,919
I mean, I have amnesia, Mr. Chris.

144
00:11:23,920 --> 00:11:26,559
I have absolutely no clue.
Please let go of me.

145
00:11:26,560 --> 00:11:27,799
Ms. Claire, I missed you.

146
00:11:27,800 --> 00:11:28,680
Mr. Chris...

147
00:11:30,920 --> 00:11:32,480
Please just let me go.

148
00:11:36,240 --> 00:11:37,479
Cha,

149
00:11:37,480 --> 00:11:38,480
it's...

150
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:40,279
not what it looks like.

151
00:11:40,280 --> 00:11:41,240
Really?

152
00:11:41,960 --> 00:11:42,880
Move.

153
00:11:43,480 --> 00:11:44,479
Claire.

154
00:11:44,480 --> 00:11:46,159
You love being a homewrecker, huh?

155
00:11:46,160 --> 00:11:47,359
No, Cha.

156
00:11:47,360 --> 00:11:48,319
No?

157
00:11:48,320 --> 00:11:49,799
Then what was that?

158
00:11:49,800 --> 00:11:51,199
- What was that?
- Cha, stop.

159
00:11:51,200 --> 00:11:53,559
- How could you?
- Cha, it's not what you think.

160
00:11:53,560 --> 00:11:54,640
Let go!

161
00:11:55,440 --> 00:11:57,159
- You bitch!
- Ms. Cha!

162
00:11:57,160 --> 00:11:59,200
- Cha, get off me!
- Stop!

163
00:12:01,440 --> 00:12:02,639
What are you doing?

164
00:12:02,640 --> 00:12:05,600
What am I doing?
Teaching this homewrecker a lesson.

165
00:12:06,960 --> 00:12:07,919
You're dead!

166
00:12:07,920 --> 00:12:10,039
- Stop it.
- Let go!

167
00:12:10,040 --> 00:12:11,119
- Stop, Ms. Cha.
- Let go!

168
00:12:11,120 --> 00:12:12,559
- I said stop.
- Let go!

169
00:12:12,560 --> 00:12:13,599
Let go!

170
00:12:13,600 --> 00:12:15,279
- Ms. Cha!
- Let go!

171
00:12:15,280 --> 00:12:16,279
Let go!

172
00:12:16,280 --> 00:12:18,840
- Pull yourself together, Ms. Cha!
- Let go!

173
00:12:22,520 --> 00:12:23,679
Did you hurt Claire?!

174
00:12:23,680 --> 00:12:25,839
Dad, ask your beloved granddaughter

175
00:12:25,840 --> 00:12:28,799
why she was hugging my boyfriend in here?

176
00:12:28,800 --> 00:12:33,720
And didn't it occur to you that your man
might actually be the one approaching her?

177
00:12:34,320 --> 00:12:38,039
You didn't actually
come here to see Ms. Cha.

178
00:12:38,040 --> 00:12:39,880
You came to see Claire, didn't you?

179
00:12:44,920 --> 00:12:45,960
Is that true, Chris?

180
00:12:47,360 --> 00:12:48,279
No, ma'am.

181
00:12:48,280 --> 00:12:50,399
I really came to see Ms. Cha.

182
00:12:50,400 --> 00:12:53,480
We had a small misunderstanding
this afternoon.

183
00:12:54,960 --> 00:12:57,519
But while I was waiting,
I saw Ms. Claire so I went to say hi.

184
00:12:57,520 --> 00:13:00,200
Then she looked
like she was going to faint,

185
00:13:01,120 --> 00:13:02,600
so I caught her.

186
00:13:05,680 --> 00:13:07,400
Well? Is that true, Claire?

187
00:13:19,520 --> 00:13:20,640
Yes, it's true.

188
00:13:21,240 --> 00:13:22,560
Chris was just helping me.

189
00:13:25,240 --> 00:13:26,720
And how are you feeling now?

190
00:13:27,360 --> 00:13:28,600
Still light-headed?

191
00:13:29,400 --> 00:13:30,320
A little bit.

192
00:13:30,920 --> 00:13:32,560
I think I'll go up and rest.

193
00:13:34,400 --> 00:13:35,680
Take her upstairs.

194
00:13:36,400 --> 00:13:37,520
Yes, sir.

195
00:13:43,320 --> 00:13:44,760
Aren't you light-headed?

196
00:14:03,560 --> 00:14:04,600
Let me take a look.

197
00:14:05,280 --> 00:14:06,200
Ow!

198
00:14:06,720 --> 00:14:09,120
Are you mad at me or something?

199
00:14:11,760 --> 00:14:13,080
Why did you say that?

200
00:14:14,840 --> 00:14:15,720
Say what?

201
00:14:18,280 --> 00:14:23,160
That story about you fainting
and Chris coming to your rescue.

202
00:14:24,800 --> 00:14:25,800
If it were Claire,

203
00:14:27,520 --> 00:14:28,520
what would she have done?

204
00:14:29,680 --> 00:14:31,880
I don't know what she would have done.

205
00:14:32,640 --> 00:14:33,920
I just wanted it to end.

206
00:14:34,520 --> 00:14:36,320
I didn't want to fight Ms. Cha.

207
00:14:37,520 --> 00:14:38,880
I felt bad for her father.

208
00:14:40,400 --> 00:14:41,640
So what really happened?

209
00:14:43,560 --> 00:14:45,720
He grabbed you, didn't he?

210
00:14:56,760 --> 00:14:59,359
Hey, let me ask you something.

211
00:14:59,360 --> 00:15:02,840
What's the deal
between Ms. Claire and Mr. Chris?

212
00:15:04,480 --> 00:15:10,120
See, I heard rumors Ms. Claire and Ms. Cha
had a huge fight over Mr. Chris.

213
00:15:11,240 --> 00:15:14,599
I'm curious because
Ms. Cha and Mr. Chris are dating,

214
00:15:14,600 --> 00:15:16,039
while Ms. Claire...

215
00:15:16,040 --> 00:15:17,679
How was she involved?

216
00:15:17,680 --> 00:15:19,679
Besides, she was engaged to you.

217
00:15:19,680 --> 00:15:22,759
And earlier, when he was hugging me,

218
00:15:22,760 --> 00:15:24,720
he said he'd missed me.

219
00:15:25,320 --> 00:15:26,760
I just don't get it.

220
00:15:28,680 --> 00:15:30,040
It's a long story.

221
00:15:30,560 --> 00:15:32,120
I'll tell you about it later.

222
00:15:33,120 --> 00:15:34,400
No "later."

223
00:15:36,920 --> 00:15:37,760
<i>Well?</i>

224
00:15:39,480 --> 00:15:40,880
Is there anything else?

225
00:15:43,400 --> 00:15:45,439
If not, please leave.

226
00:15:45,440 --> 00:15:47,920
And don't cause any more trouble here.

227
00:15:49,920 --> 00:15:51,080
Yes, ma'am.

228
00:15:52,640 --> 00:15:53,800
Let's go, honey.

229
00:15:58,640 --> 00:15:59,839
Cha.

230
00:15:59,840 --> 00:16:00,879
Wait a minute.

231
00:16:00,880 --> 00:16:02,200
Let go of me.

232
00:16:03,120 --> 00:16:04,959
I have nothing to say to you.

233
00:16:04,960 --> 00:16:06,040
Just leave.

234
00:16:07,040 --> 00:16:08,640
- Cha.
- Let go.

235
00:16:12,400 --> 00:16:13,880
<i>Tell me right now.</i>

236
00:16:14,840 --> 00:16:16,440
What was their relationship?

237
00:16:24,560 --> 00:16:25,720
Hello.

238
00:16:28,400 --> 00:16:30,040
Are you the new architect?

239
00:16:31,200 --> 00:16:32,159
Yes, I am.

240
00:16:32,160 --> 00:16:33,240
What's your name?

241
00:16:34,040 --> 00:16:35,240
My name is Chris.

242
00:16:39,120 --> 00:16:41,160
Take a look at these for me.

243
00:16:41,920 --> 00:16:43,000
Which one suits me best?

244
00:16:58,760 --> 00:17:01,880
Professionally speaking, as an architect...

245
00:17:02,800 --> 00:17:03,720
I'd say...

246
00:17:04,760 --> 00:17:06,319
this one looks best on you.

247
00:17:09,319 --> 00:17:11,359
What if you weren't
speaking as an architect?

248
00:17:12,280 --> 00:17:14,960
Then in what capacity should I answer?

249
00:17:18,640 --> 00:17:19,720
Well...

250
00:17:20,760 --> 00:17:22,720
I'd want you to answer...

251
00:17:24,200 --> 00:17:25,680
as a man.

252
00:17:26,640 --> 00:17:29,440
Speaking as a man...

253
00:17:30,520 --> 00:17:33,280
you'd look best wearing nothing at all.

254
00:18:15,680 --> 00:18:16,680
What is it?

255
00:18:21,640 --> 00:18:23,560
I've never been happier, you know?

256
00:18:24,400 --> 00:18:25,680
Are you sure?

257
00:18:29,960 --> 00:18:31,080
Why?

258
00:18:36,360 --> 00:18:38,280
It's good that you're happy.

259
00:18:43,720 --> 00:18:45,320
What do you mean by that?

260
00:18:46,280 --> 00:18:47,640
Chris?

261
00:18:48,720 --> 00:18:49,880
Chris?

262
00:18:51,440 --> 00:18:52,480
Chris!

263
00:18:57,400 --> 00:18:58,640
Chris!

264
00:18:59,440 --> 00:19:00,360
Chris!

265
00:19:01,800 --> 00:19:02,840
Cha.

266
00:19:05,480 --> 00:19:06,760
What are you doing here?

267
00:19:08,480 --> 00:19:11,040
I was afraid
she wouldn't believe we were together,

268
00:19:12,000 --> 00:19:13,920
so I wanted her to see it for herself.

269
00:19:14,800 --> 00:19:17,679
Enjoy your boyfriend. I'm done using him.

270
00:19:17,680 --> 00:19:18,720
You bitch.

271
00:19:27,320 --> 00:19:31,240
Let's see if a bullet
can stop your madness.

272
00:19:32,040 --> 00:19:33,640
Think I'm scared of you?

273
00:19:34,480 --> 00:19:36,239
Ms. Claire, calm down.

274
00:19:36,240 --> 00:19:37,440
Cha, don't do this.

275
00:19:45,040 --> 00:19:46,880
Instead of freaking out on me,

276
00:19:47,840 --> 00:19:50,159
you should thank me

277
00:19:50,160 --> 00:19:52,400
for not actually wanting your man.

278
00:19:54,880 --> 00:19:55,960
Why did you do this?

279
00:19:57,880 --> 00:19:58,880
Why?

280
00:20:05,640 --> 00:20:07,360
Because I wanted you to know...

281
00:20:08,080 --> 00:20:09,520
that you...

282
00:20:10,280 --> 00:20:12,080
can never beat me.

283
00:20:58,520 --> 00:21:00,440
<i>So everything Ms. Claire did</i>

284
00:21:01,120 --> 00:21:03,200
was just to beat Ms. Cha?

285
00:21:07,320 --> 00:21:11,640
I mean, I knew
she was spoiled and competitive,

286
00:21:12,440 --> 00:21:14,319
but I never thought...

287
00:21:14,320 --> 00:21:16,600
she'd go so far as using her own body.

288
00:21:18,600 --> 00:21:20,040
She did far worse.

289
00:21:28,960 --> 00:21:31,120
What else is in store for me?

290
00:21:34,320 --> 00:21:35,920
You said she'd done worse.

291
00:21:36,760 --> 00:21:39,720
What else don't I know? Tell me.

292
00:21:41,520 --> 00:21:43,000
Tell me.

293
00:21:46,400 --> 00:21:47,599
Why?

294
00:21:47,600 --> 00:21:50,719
Why do I have to
answer for something I didn't do?

295
00:21:50,720 --> 00:21:52,800
And how could you stand it?

296
00:21:53,680 --> 00:21:55,319
You were her fiancé.

297
00:21:55,320 --> 00:21:57,239
She slept with someone else,

298
00:21:57,240 --> 00:21:59,319
yet you don't feel anything.

299
00:21:59,320 --> 00:22:00,640
How do you do it?

300
00:22:03,600 --> 00:22:06,840
Just because I don't speak
doesn't mean I feel nothing.

301
00:22:08,600 --> 00:22:11,920
Just know our love
wasn't like anyone else's.

302
00:22:13,160 --> 00:22:14,960
That's all you need to know.

303
00:22:38,080 --> 00:22:39,960
Hey, where do you think you're going?

304
00:22:41,000 --> 00:22:43,319
If you want to drink, do it here at home.

305
00:22:43,320 --> 00:22:44,679
Don't go out and make a scene.

306
00:22:44,680 --> 00:22:45,919
No.

307
00:22:45,920 --> 00:22:48,759
I'm going out
because I don't want to stay here.

308
00:22:48,760 --> 00:22:52,919
I won't live under the same roof
or breathe the same air as her.

309
00:22:52,920 --> 00:22:55,479
Do you know what I want to do right now?

310
00:22:55,480 --> 00:22:57,119
I want to kill her.

311
00:22:57,120 --> 00:22:58,360
Cha!

312
00:22:59,520 --> 00:23:01,360
Stop crying over a single guy!

313
00:23:01,960 --> 00:23:04,879
I told you to dump him.
He doesn't love you.

314
00:23:04,880 --> 00:23:07,119
So you're saying he loves Claire?

315
00:23:07,120 --> 00:23:08,719
No way.

316
00:23:08,720 --> 00:23:10,119
He loves me.

317
00:23:10,120 --> 00:23:12,519
He's like this
because she manipulated him.

318
00:23:12,520 --> 00:23:13,520
Look,

319
00:23:14,040 --> 00:23:18,080
I'm telling you this
because you need to focus on the company.

320
00:23:18,680 --> 00:23:22,439
If you let Claire crawl back
into it, you'll be left with nothing.

321
00:23:22,440 --> 00:23:24,040
Don't worry, Mom.

322
00:23:25,200 --> 00:23:28,320
I'll never hand over
the company or Chris to her.

323
00:23:29,480 --> 00:23:31,080
But you have to help me.

324
00:23:31,680 --> 00:23:33,600
You have to help me convince Dad.

325
00:23:34,920 --> 00:23:36,040
About what?

326
00:23:51,000 --> 00:23:54,199
<i>Claire, you love being a homewrecker, huh?</i>

327
00:23:54,200 --> 00:23:55,959
- No, Cha.
- No?

328
00:23:55,960 --> 00:23:57,999
- Then what was that? How could you?
- Cha.

329
00:23:58,000 --> 00:23:59,399
- Cha, stop.
- It's not what you think.

330
00:23:59,400 --> 00:24:00,560
Let go!

331
00:24:22,520 --> 00:24:24,560
He wants me to think like Ms. Claire.

332
00:24:25,680 --> 00:24:27,440
I can never do it.

333
00:24:29,120 --> 00:24:33,920
I would never get involved with
someone who's already taken, like she did.

334
00:24:47,600 --> 00:24:49,040
Do you have a minute?

335
00:24:51,800 --> 00:24:53,480
Can we talk?

336
00:25:00,240 --> 00:25:01,480
What is it?

337
00:25:03,320 --> 00:25:04,960
I want to talk about Chris.

338
00:25:05,800 --> 00:25:07,480
I have nothing to say to you.

339
00:25:08,840 --> 00:25:10,640
Can we let bygones be bygones?

340
00:25:14,880 --> 00:25:16,080
What did you say?

341
00:25:17,080 --> 00:25:20,359
I know I've done
terrible things in the past,

342
00:25:20,360 --> 00:25:22,879
but I'm not that person anymore.

343
00:25:22,880 --> 00:25:24,560
So I wanted to ask if we could...

344
00:25:27,560 --> 00:25:30,680
well, if we could try to be friends?

345
00:25:32,680 --> 00:25:33,919
What are you doing?

346
00:25:33,920 --> 00:25:35,679
I'm not doing anything.

347
00:25:35,680 --> 00:25:38,160
I just really want all of this to end.

348
00:25:38,800 --> 00:25:41,159
You know I have
amnesia because of the crash.

349
00:25:41,160 --> 00:25:44,399
I thought we could use this
as a chance for a fresh start.

350
00:25:44,400 --> 00:25:45,320
What do you say?

351
00:25:52,000 --> 00:25:54,400
So are you suffering from
memory loss or insanity?

352
00:25:55,320 --> 00:25:57,680
Even if you don't remember
the awful things you did,

353
00:25:58,280 --> 00:25:59,880
I will never forget them.

354
00:26:00,840 --> 00:26:01,840
Hey.

355
00:26:04,560 --> 00:26:06,840
What if I promise to stay away from Chris?

356
00:26:09,720 --> 00:26:11,639
I know that's why you're mad at me.

357
00:26:11,640 --> 00:26:15,520
But I swear whatever
happened between me and him ends now.

358
00:26:17,840 --> 00:26:18,920
Isn't that nice?

359
00:26:20,320 --> 00:26:23,200
You lost your memory,
but found a conscience.

360
00:26:24,520 --> 00:26:27,279
Fine. If you can actually do it, great.

361
00:26:27,280 --> 00:26:28,600
I'll be watching.

362
00:26:37,640 --> 00:26:39,599
If I start treating her well,

363
00:26:39,600 --> 00:26:41,520
someday she'll return the favor.

364
00:27:25,000 --> 00:27:26,719
<i>You were her fiancé.</i>

365
00:27:26,720 --> 00:27:28,199
<i>She slept with someone else,</i>

366
00:27:28,200 --> 00:27:30,199
<i>yet you don't feel anything.</i>

367
00:27:30,200 --> 00:27:31,759
<i>How do you do it?</i>

368
00:27:31,760 --> 00:27:35,080
<i>Just know our love
wasn't like anyone else's.</i>

369
00:27:35,600 --> 00:27:37,280
<i>That's all you need to know.</i>

370
00:27:51,520 --> 00:27:52,880
Hello?

371
00:27:57,200 --> 00:27:58,680
Is this his house?

372
00:28:02,880 --> 00:28:04,560
Anyone home?

373
00:28:36,080 --> 00:28:37,280
What are you doing here?

374
00:28:44,240 --> 00:28:46,399
Well, I...

375
00:28:46,400 --> 00:28:47,560
I'm sorry.

376
00:28:48,560 --> 00:28:50,479
You said you lived in another house,

377
00:28:50,480 --> 00:28:52,520
- so I--
- I asked why you were here.

378
00:28:56,960 --> 00:28:59,479
I wanted to borrow a cellphone

379
00:28:59,480 --> 00:29:01,080
to check my Facebook.

380
00:29:02,240 --> 00:29:06,720
I didn't do anything bad.
I just wanted to see my own face.

381
00:29:07,600 --> 00:29:10,080
I'm terrified
I'll forget what I looked like.

382
00:29:26,440 --> 00:29:28,720
Tun, she's inside my house.

383
00:29:29,240 --> 00:29:30,760
How could you let her slip by?

384
00:29:32,200 --> 00:29:37,159
Look, I already told you
I just wanted to see pictures of myself.

385
00:29:37,160 --> 00:29:38,160
Get out.

386
00:29:41,080 --> 00:29:43,240
Stop treating me like your slave.

387
00:29:43,760 --> 00:29:45,679
Actually, you should be nicer to me.

388
00:29:45,680 --> 00:29:48,840
Because without me,
what would you do, huh?

389
00:29:58,080 --> 00:29:58,920
Then leave.

390
00:30:01,680 --> 00:30:02,680
Do you want to leave?

391
00:30:06,080 --> 00:30:07,600
You can still leave.

392
00:30:13,400 --> 00:30:14,600
You're not leaving?

393
00:30:17,160 --> 00:30:21,000
Next time, if you don't mean
what you say, then don't say it.

394
00:30:22,040 --> 00:30:23,720
I don't like being threatened.

395
00:30:28,240 --> 00:30:30,440
Drop the attitude already.

396
00:30:31,040 --> 00:30:32,800
Can't you be decent for once?

397
00:30:34,560 --> 00:30:39,479
You know, Ms. Cha isn't
actually as bad as you think.

398
00:30:39,480 --> 00:30:42,840
If we treat her right,
she'll return the favor.

399
00:30:44,920 --> 00:30:46,240
What do you mean by that?

400
00:30:47,240 --> 00:30:48,240
What did you do?

401
00:30:49,200 --> 00:30:53,400
I just promised her that I would
stay away from her boyfriend, Chris.

402
00:30:54,600 --> 00:30:55,960
That was enough for her.

403
00:30:58,360 --> 00:31:00,159
Who said you could do that?

404
00:31:00,160 --> 00:31:03,559
Didn't I tell you never to
do anything without my orders?!

405
00:31:03,560 --> 00:31:07,760
Hey! Instead of yelling at me,
you should be thanking me.

406
00:31:08,360 --> 00:31:10,639
For stopping
Ms. Cha from being cruel to me,

407
00:31:10,640 --> 00:31:14,600
and for making sure you don't
look like a fiancé who's being cheated on.

408
00:31:16,640 --> 00:31:18,920
- Get out. Leave.
- Hey, stop.

409
00:31:20,000 --> 00:31:21,040
That hurts.

410
00:31:21,560 --> 00:31:25,159
Leave before I completely lose my temper.

411
00:31:25,160 --> 00:31:26,359
What's wrong with you?

412
00:31:26,360 --> 00:31:27,599
Nothing I do is right.

413
00:31:27,600 --> 00:31:30,039
Because Claire
would never do those things.

414
00:31:30,040 --> 00:31:31,760
- I'm not her!
- Hey.

415
00:31:32,680 --> 00:31:35,400
What would happen
if someone overheard what you just said?

416
00:31:36,120 --> 00:31:37,800
Chan, what's going on?

417
00:31:39,880 --> 00:31:41,240
Why did you need him?

418
00:31:43,440 --> 00:31:44,680
Take her out of here.

419
00:31:45,520 --> 00:31:47,120
And don't let her back here.

420
00:31:48,360 --> 00:31:50,040
As if I wanted to be here.

421
00:31:52,400 --> 00:31:53,240
Please.

422
00:32:01,480 --> 00:32:02,520
Hey.

423
00:32:04,400 --> 00:32:05,600
Seriously,

424
00:32:06,240 --> 00:32:08,079
is your boss a psychopath?

425
00:32:08,080 --> 00:32:11,480
I just wanted to borrow a phone.
No need to blow a fuse.

426
00:32:13,560 --> 00:32:16,040
Chan hates it
when people come here unannounced.

427
00:32:17,720 --> 00:32:19,640
As if I wanted to be anywhere near it.

428
00:32:21,480 --> 00:32:22,599
By the way...

429
00:32:22,600 --> 00:32:26,879
At first, I wondered how
someone like him ended up with Claire.

430
00:32:26,880 --> 00:32:30,039
But you know what? Now I wonder

431
00:32:30,040 --> 00:32:32,480
how she got engaged to a guy like him.

432
00:32:35,600 --> 00:32:37,279
They weren't in love, right?

433
00:32:37,280 --> 00:32:39,480
They were engaged,

434
00:32:40,000 --> 00:32:43,080
but when I was inside,
there wasn't a single couples photo.

435
00:32:43,880 --> 00:32:46,119
When you love someone

436
00:32:46,120 --> 00:32:48,039
and they come up in conversation,

437
00:32:48,040 --> 00:32:51,919
there should at least be
a hint of affection for them.

438
00:32:51,920 --> 00:32:55,280
But I don't see anything
like that in him toward her.

439
00:32:55,880 --> 00:32:57,040
And what did he say?

440
00:32:58,160 --> 00:33:00,639
He said that's just how their love was.

441
00:33:00,640 --> 00:33:01,840
Hm.

442
00:33:02,840 --> 00:33:04,080
It's like he said.

443
00:33:05,080 --> 00:33:06,839
Love comes in many forms.

444
00:33:06,840 --> 00:33:09,640
You may be used to
outward displays of affection,

445
00:33:10,360 --> 00:33:13,520
but it doesn't mean those
who are different don't love each other.

446
00:33:14,520 --> 00:33:16,400
- But still...
- Trust me.

447
00:33:17,520 --> 00:33:19,800
No one loved Ms. Claire more than Chan.

448
00:33:23,160 --> 00:33:24,360
After you.

449
00:33:29,640 --> 00:33:30,599
Please.

450
00:33:30,600 --> 00:33:31,680
I get it.

451
00:33:58,360 --> 00:33:59,680
<i>Put it on me.</i>

452
00:34:06,440 --> 00:34:09,639
<i>When you grow up,
you can't marry anyone but me.</i>

453
00:34:10,960 --> 00:34:12,080
<i>Promise me.</i>

454
00:34:12,600 --> 00:34:14,080
<i>I promise.</i>

455
00:34:31,520 --> 00:34:33,199
I dropped her off safely.

456
00:34:35,760 --> 00:34:37,960
Did she suspect anything?

457
00:34:39,679 --> 00:34:42,960
She questioned why
you and Ms. Claire didn't seem in love.

458
00:34:44,000 --> 00:34:48,040
So I told her people have
different ways of showing affection.

459
00:34:55,239 --> 00:34:56,440
But right now,

460
00:34:57,000 --> 00:34:58,800
the one I'm most worried about...

461
00:34:59,880 --> 00:35:01,040
is you.

462
00:35:03,040 --> 00:35:05,240
About Chris coming over last night...

463
00:35:07,360 --> 00:35:08,360
It was nothing.

464
00:35:09,600 --> 00:35:11,800
You know exactly how Claire was.

465
00:35:13,600 --> 00:35:15,520
The pathetic one is Chris.

466
00:35:16,320 --> 00:35:20,240
He didn't even realize
Claire was just using him to beat Ms. Cha.

467
00:35:27,200 --> 00:35:29,400
It's been a while since we sparred.

468
00:35:31,000 --> 00:35:32,400
How about we do that today?

469
00:36:14,600 --> 00:36:15,640
Well?

470
00:36:16,360 --> 00:36:18,800
Did blowing off some steam
clear your head?

471
00:36:21,080 --> 00:36:22,080
Clear my head?

472
00:36:25,040 --> 00:36:28,000
You're frustrated because of Chris.

473
00:36:28,680 --> 00:36:29,879
Why would I be?

474
00:36:29,880 --> 00:36:32,400
She's not Claire.

475
00:36:36,080 --> 00:36:41,039
You know
how I can tell you're furious right now?

476
00:36:41,040 --> 00:36:45,360
Don't forget I grew up
with you and Ms. Claire.

477
00:36:46,320 --> 00:36:49,519
Whenever you box
or push yourself in the gym,

478
00:36:49,520 --> 00:36:53,560
you do it to vent the feelings
you can't put into words.

479
00:36:55,560 --> 00:37:00,440
And I've seen you box every day
since Ms. Claire passed away.

480
00:37:03,720 --> 00:37:06,960
If you're done psychoanalyzing me,
go back and watch her.

481
00:37:07,520 --> 00:37:09,680
I don't want her causing any more trouble.

482
00:37:12,120 --> 00:37:15,839
Do you know why
that night I wanted you to be sure

483
00:37:15,840 --> 00:37:18,880
you wanted to give her Ms. Claire's face?

484
00:37:19,560 --> 00:37:22,039
Because once we did that,

485
00:37:22,040 --> 00:37:24,280
you'd have to see her face every day.

486
00:37:24,920 --> 00:37:27,440
And you'd be the one hurting the most.

487
00:37:32,720 --> 00:37:34,000
I'm perfectly fine.

488
00:37:35,080 --> 00:37:36,120
Thanks anyway.

489
00:37:39,960 --> 00:37:42,519
Whenever you want to go another round,

490
00:37:42,520 --> 00:37:44,640
just call me. I'm always ready.

491
00:38:01,320 --> 00:38:03,280
NEUROLOGY HOSPITAL

492
00:38:14,000 --> 00:38:14,840
Hello?

493
00:38:16,800 --> 00:38:19,920
Yes, that's right.
I'm a relative of Ms. Nalin.

494
00:38:23,000 --> 00:38:24,120
What did you say?

495
00:38:24,960 --> 00:38:26,560
What happened to her?

496
00:38:35,720 --> 00:38:38,160
ALICHA BUNPHITHAK, NITCHAN SATHITPHONG

497
00:38:41,640 --> 00:38:42,760
CHRIS PRACHAKCHAI

498
00:38:46,160 --> 00:38:47,200
Mr. Chris...

499
00:38:49,200 --> 00:38:51,720
Ms. Claire, I was so worried about you.

500
00:38:54,360 --> 00:38:55,399
Please let go of me.

501
00:38:55,400 --> 00:38:57,039
It's not what it looks like.

502
00:38:57,040 --> 00:38:58,040
Really?

503
00:39:00,880 --> 00:39:03,600
I used to think you were such a great guy.

504
00:39:05,640 --> 00:39:07,840
But what you did last night...

505
00:39:13,320 --> 00:39:15,880
Claire, it's me, your grandpa!

506
00:39:20,360 --> 00:39:21,480
Claire?

507
00:39:22,520 --> 00:39:23,800
Yes, Grandpa!

508
00:39:27,080 --> 00:39:28,600
I'm coming! I'm coming!

509
00:39:38,080 --> 00:39:38,920
Grandpa.

510
00:39:40,840 --> 00:39:41,920
What are you up to?

511
00:39:42,600 --> 00:39:44,119
Did I interrupt anything?

512
00:39:44,120 --> 00:39:46,239
Oh, not at all.

513
00:39:46,240 --> 00:39:48,040
Did you need anything?

514
00:39:48,560 --> 00:39:50,999
You could've sent someone to get me.

515
00:39:51,000 --> 00:39:53,079
Oh, it's fine.

516
00:39:53,080 --> 00:39:56,120
I can manage a short walk.
My heart's still strong.

517
00:39:58,600 --> 00:40:01,080
So, have you recovered from the scare?

518
00:40:02,280 --> 00:40:03,160
The scare?

519
00:40:03,720 --> 00:40:05,920
You know, from last night.

520
00:40:06,960 --> 00:40:07,960
Oh, right.

521
00:40:08,680 --> 00:40:09,919
I'm all better now.

522
00:40:09,920 --> 00:40:11,560
If it weren't for...

523
00:40:12,640 --> 00:40:14,280
your amnesia,

524
00:40:14,880 --> 00:40:17,160
I wouldn't have come
to warn you about Chris.

525
00:40:18,160 --> 00:40:21,319
I don't want you involved
with someone who's taken.

526
00:40:21,320 --> 00:40:24,639
Especially since that man is dating Cha.

527
00:40:24,640 --> 00:40:27,040
No matter how much I love you,

528
00:40:29,360 --> 00:40:31,600
I deeply understand how she feels.

529
00:40:32,640 --> 00:40:35,959
Nothing cuts deeper than finding out

530
00:40:35,960 --> 00:40:38,520
the one you love is cheating on you.

531
00:40:40,800 --> 00:40:41,840
I know, Grandpa.

532
00:40:43,400 --> 00:40:46,519
I already talked to Cha.
I assured her it won't happen again.

533
00:40:46,520 --> 00:40:48,439
You actually talked to her?

534
00:40:48,440 --> 00:40:51,840
Yes. I know what I did was wrong.

535
00:40:57,240 --> 00:40:59,200
Uh, Grandpa...

536
00:41:00,520 --> 00:41:02,160
Are you upset with me?

537
00:41:03,640 --> 00:41:04,680
Not at all.

538
00:41:06,600 --> 00:41:07,880
I'm just not used to this.

539
00:41:09,560 --> 00:41:12,920
I never expected to hear
these words coming from you.

540
00:41:14,440 --> 00:41:17,919
But then again,
maybe losing your memory is a blessing.

541
00:41:17,920 --> 00:41:21,359
Otherwise,
you'd probably be tearing the house down

542
00:41:21,360 --> 00:41:23,600
because you never let anyone win.

543
00:41:26,040 --> 00:41:27,400
Yes, that's true.

544
00:41:28,520 --> 00:41:31,239
Everything has a silver lining, really.

545
00:41:31,240 --> 00:41:32,960
It depends on how you look at it.

546
00:41:36,120 --> 00:41:39,960
If you don't have any plans today,
want to go for a drive with me?

547
00:41:46,040 --> 00:41:47,440
<i>Ms. Cha's not there yet?</i>

548
00:41:51,600 --> 00:41:53,560
If she shows up, give me a call.

549
00:42:02,040 --> 00:42:03,919
A<i>JISHA</i> SHA

550
00:42:03,920 --> 00:42:05,200
Cha?

551
00:42:15,880 --> 00:42:16,720
Cha.

552
00:42:18,920 --> 00:42:20,440
You're not mad anymore, right?

553
00:42:21,640 --> 00:42:22,760
What makes you say that?

554
00:42:23,720 --> 00:42:26,240
Just because
I didn't wipe our photos off IG?

555
00:42:27,240 --> 00:42:30,240
Deleting pictures
after a breakup is so childish.

556
00:42:31,120 --> 00:42:32,720
If I want to end things,

557
00:42:34,160 --> 00:42:35,840
I'll say it right to your face.

558
00:42:36,920 --> 00:42:39,000
Cha, I am so sorry.

559
00:42:40,080 --> 00:42:41,640
For causing a misunderstanding.

560
00:42:42,800 --> 00:42:44,359
And what did I misunderstand?

561
00:42:44,360 --> 00:42:45,600
About Ms. Claire, of course

562
00:42:46,680 --> 00:42:48,240
You have to believe me.

563
00:42:50,120 --> 00:42:51,280
Believe you?

564
00:42:52,040 --> 00:42:55,759
If you want me
to believe you, do as I say.

565
00:42:55,760 --> 00:42:58,279
I will. Just tell me, Cha.

566
00:42:58,280 --> 00:42:59,880
I'll do anything for you.

567
00:43:07,680 --> 00:43:08,960
Go kill her for me.

568
00:43:09,600 --> 00:43:10,600
What?

569
00:43:11,760 --> 00:43:13,039
Why?

570
00:43:13,040 --> 00:43:14,000
You can't do it?

571
00:43:15,920 --> 00:43:18,640
Or would you rather die in her place?

572
00:43:22,680 --> 00:43:24,720
Cha! Let go, Cha!

573
00:43:26,800 --> 00:43:27,719
Cha!

574
00:43:27,720 --> 00:43:29,199
Let go, Cha!

575
00:43:29,200 --> 00:43:30,360
Cha!

576
00:43:39,600 --> 00:43:41,200
I was just kidding.

577
00:43:41,800 --> 00:43:44,520
I could never hurt the one I love.

578
00:43:45,960 --> 00:43:48,560
Okay, I'm not mad anymore.

579
00:43:51,040 --> 00:43:52,680
Go get changed, Chris.

580
00:43:57,880 --> 00:44:00,320
Okay. Give me a few minutes.

581
00:44:25,200 --> 00:44:26,080
Is something wrong?

582
00:44:28,800 --> 00:44:29,840
No.

583
00:44:34,880 --> 00:44:35,880
I understand.

584
00:44:36,600 --> 00:44:40,520
Sometimes people with
amnesia feel that something's off.

585
00:44:41,360 --> 00:44:42,440
Right?

586
00:44:45,120 --> 00:44:47,200
Have you been able to recall anything?

587
00:44:49,760 --> 00:44:50,600
Not yet.

588
00:45:00,440 --> 00:45:02,320
Is there something on your mind?

589
00:45:03,320 --> 00:45:04,680
It's nothing.

590
00:45:07,160 --> 00:45:10,280
I remember that before the crash,

591
00:45:10,880 --> 00:45:13,320
you said you had
something really important to tell me.

592
00:45:14,880 --> 00:45:17,880
So I thought I'd ask,
in case you remembered something.

593
00:45:21,440 --> 00:45:22,719
And...

594
00:45:22,720 --> 00:45:27,159
do you have any idea
what it could be about, Grandpa?

595
00:45:27,160 --> 00:45:30,880
<i>It's been days.
Have you still not talked to Claire?</i>

596
00:45:31,600 --> 00:45:33,920
You guys fought over me again, didn't you?

597
00:45:38,000 --> 00:45:40,080
I apologize on Claire's behalf.

598
00:45:41,560 --> 00:45:42,840
I'm not mad.

599
00:45:44,200 --> 00:45:49,960
But it's best you tell her
to stop behaving like this.

600
00:45:51,440 --> 00:45:55,560
Because I'm worried about your heart.

601
00:46:00,680 --> 00:46:01,520
Rin...

602
00:46:03,720 --> 00:46:06,080
Ugh, still using the same tactics?

603
00:46:07,000 --> 00:46:11,000
Every time there's trouble,
you get all seductive on him.

604
00:46:11,600 --> 00:46:14,639
At first,
I thought you married a housekeeper.

605
00:46:14,640 --> 00:46:15,560
But I was wrong.

606
00:46:17,160 --> 00:46:18,680
She's actually a whore.

607
00:46:20,120 --> 00:46:21,479
Claire!

608
00:46:21,480 --> 00:46:23,599
Stop going after Aunt Rin, will you?

609
00:46:23,600 --> 00:46:25,719
I've never seen her go after you.

610
00:46:25,720 --> 00:46:27,160
Are you sure...

611
00:46:27,800 --> 00:46:29,240
she didn't do anything?

612
00:46:30,000 --> 00:46:31,400
What do you mean by that?

613
00:46:32,080 --> 00:46:33,160
I did nothing.

614
00:46:33,760 --> 00:46:37,840
I know you don't like me,
but don't make things up about me.

615
00:46:39,400 --> 00:46:41,040
I think it's best I leave.

616
00:46:45,240 --> 00:46:49,680
Whatever you say,
watch out for your grandfather's heart.

617
00:46:56,680 --> 00:46:57,760
See that, Claire?

618
00:46:58,560 --> 00:47:00,000
Aunt Rin cares about me.

619
00:47:00,920 --> 00:47:03,559
Drop these delusions of yours about her.

620
00:47:03,560 --> 00:47:05,199
Okay.

621
00:47:05,200 --> 00:47:06,800
I'll take it back.

622
00:47:07,720 --> 00:47:09,920
She didn't do anything to me or you.

623
00:47:10,760 --> 00:47:11,760
But to her lover.

624
00:47:13,840 --> 00:47:15,239
Watch your mouth, Claire?!

625
00:47:15,240 --> 00:47:17,439
She would never cheat.

626
00:47:17,440 --> 00:47:19,080
What if I have proof?

627
00:47:24,240 --> 00:47:25,080
It's nothing.

628
00:47:27,760 --> 00:47:31,360
But if you remember anything,
just let me know.

629
00:47:34,680 --> 00:47:35,560
I will.

630
00:47:44,080 --> 00:47:45,159
So...

631
00:47:45,160 --> 00:47:48,160
where are we going?

632
00:47:49,840 --> 00:47:51,360
To your favorite place.

633
00:48:21,480 --> 00:48:23,199
<i>What kind of soup is this?</i>

634
00:48:23,200 --> 00:48:26,399
It's lobster soup with white wine sauce.

635
00:48:26,400 --> 00:48:27,720
I'm allergic to shellfish.

636
00:48:28,760 --> 00:48:30,039
Claire!

637
00:48:30,040 --> 00:48:31,519
<i>You think she was lying?</i>

638
00:48:31,520 --> 00:48:33,799
Has she ever had a shellfish allergy, Mom?

639
00:48:33,800 --> 00:48:37,119
<i>Ms. Cha probably wants to show
that even if Claire is fine,</i>

640
00:48:37,120 --> 00:48:39,039
<i>she's still unfit to run the company.</i>

641
00:48:39,040 --> 00:48:40,399
<i>Stop thinking that way.</i>

642
00:48:40,400 --> 00:48:45,079
I will never let you take over my company!

643
00:48:45,080 --> 00:48:47,360
<i>Since Dad isn't giving us anything,</i>

644
00:48:47,960 --> 00:48:49,680
<i>we have to take it ourselves.</i>
